              <a name="61914"></a><h1>Holiday Playschemes</h1>





<h2>Holiday Playschemes</h2>
<p>The University works in partnership with playscheme providers to support families during the school holiday periods. Please see information below for provider details.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Create Holiday Club Oxford Montessori Schools (Forest Farm)</strong></p>
<p>'Create' has now been successfully running for over 5 years. &nbsp; We employ qualified teachers, so the children can learn as well as have fun at the playscheme. &nbsp;&lsquo;Create&rsquo; takes place at Forest Farm, our farm school environment in Elsfield. &nbsp;We cook, paint, walk, take part in drama, music and dance, learn bushcraft skills and care for animals (our ponies, hens &amp; peacock). &nbsp;Our history teacher Taryn leads special workshops during the summer holidays and, as she is also a costume maker, the children are able to dress up in period costumes.&nbsp; They adore playing Tudors or Elizabethans for the day. &nbsp;There is a bus services from various destinations in central Oxford.&nbsp; Please click <a href="http://www.oxfordmontessori.co.uk/#/forest-farm-create/" title="OMS Create">Oxford Montessori Create</a> for further information.<br /><br />Please follow the link: <a href="http://www.oxfordmontessori.co.uk/">Create Holiday Club</a>.&nbsp; Click <a href="http://www.oxfordmontessori.co.uk/create-holiday-club-bookings?utm_source=General&amp;utm_campaign=7fd6aa7bf4-Create+News&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_term=0_8499788653-7fd6aa7bf4-28553789" title="OMS">here</a> to book.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Mini-Media </strong></p>
<p>Mini-Media is a&nbsp;holiday playscheme&nbsp;with exciting art adventure days workshops.&nbsp; Further information can be found at&nbsp;&nbsp;<a  href="/media/global/wwwadminoxacuk/localsites/childcare/documents/Workshop_Info_Mini-Media2_.pdf" title="Mini-Media Information">Mini-Media Information</a> <img class="fileIcon" height="15" width="15" src="/media/global/fileicons/pdf.gif" alt="" /> (320kb).&nbsp; Please click <a href="http://mini-mediakids.com/" title="Mini-Media Kids">Mini-Media </a>to view&nbsp;website.</p>
<p>We are running our art and adventure creative workshops on two days of the the first week of the Easter holidays. Our exciting outdoor and indoor creative craft activities include: nature diary; creative shelter and den building; pottery;&nbsp;painting abstracts; mini stuffed toys to make and sew; and lots more</p>
<p><strong>Mini-Media Creative Art &amp; Adventure Days Workshop</strong></p>
<p><strong>St.Michael's School Tuesday 31st&nbsp;March and Wednesday April 1st 2015</strong></p>
<p>9.30 - 4.30pm &pound;30 per child per day sibling discounts for early booking.</p>
<p>Sibling discounts for early booking</p>
<p><strong>For bookings please email us as soon as possible&nbsp;to reserve your place: <a href="mailto:info@mini-mediakids.com">info@mini-mediakids.com</a></strong><strong></strong></p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Ultimate Activity Camps &ndash; 15% off for Oxford University staff: active camps</strong></p>
<p>Ultimate Activity Camps are an Oxford-based provider of premium activity holiday day camps for children aged 4-14, with camps running at Headington School and Beachborough School (Brackley). Run by a team with over 25 years&rsquo; experience of running high quality activity camps, children will have the opportunity to have try over 40 exciting activities each week, meet friends and learn new skills.</p>
<p>We have learnt that there are three magic ingredients for the Ultimate Activity Camp - inspiring and friendly staff, exciting activities and fantastic facilities - we will deliver this every day, and in every activity. From motor quads and fencing, to ultimate inflatables and swimming, Ultimate Activity Camps are bursting with fantastic activities &ndash; they&rsquo;ll wish the day was longer!</p>
<p>Our camps are Ofsted registered, our staff are CRB cleared and we accept Childcare vouchers as payment. We are so confident that your child will have a great experience on camp, that we offer a money-back &lsquo;Ultimate Guarantee&rsquo;.</p>
<p><strong>Oxford University staff receive 15% off standard rates - for more information, visit <a href="http://www.ultimateactivity.co.uk/">http://www.ultimateactivity.co.uk/</a>or to make a booking call 0844 870 7077.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Schools of Sport &ndash; elite sports coaching for boys and girls aged 7-16: 15% off for Oxford University staff</strong> <br /><br />Get set for sport this summer with Schools of Sport who offer an exceptional opportunity for Oxford&rsquo;s young sportsmen and women aged 7 to 16 to experience elite sports coaching in cutting-edge skills and strategies, direct from some of the country&rsquo;s leading coaches and sports people. Run during the school holidays at outstanding facilities around Oxford, children will leave our academies with new skills and totally inspired. Our coaches don&rsquo;t just put their names to the programmes they create; they work with Schools of Sport to coach every child on the course and take a close personal interest in the quality of the academy experience. Head Coaches are joined in delivering their programmes by a team of highly qualified and experienced assistants.&nbsp;</p>
<p><br />For more information visit <a href="http://www.schoolsofsport.co.uk/">www.schoolsofsport.co.uk</a> and call <strong>0844 870 9077 </strong>to receive your 15% staff discount (off standard rates).</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Oxford Active</strong>: Active Camps</p>
<p>Active Camps provide school holiday camps for children. Whether your child wants to join us for one day, one week or the entire holiday, our wide range of fun and exciting activities will be something they remember forever.</p>
<p>Our camps are located in local schools with fantastic facilities &ndash; both indoor and out. Combine that with our vast array of equipment and activities and your child will be envy of all their friends&hellip;if they&rsquo;re not already on the same camp!</p>
<p>Our activities change daily, weekly and monthly so your kids will never get bored. Drama and dance, arts and crafts, all types of sport both traditional and wacky, assault courses, archery, canoeing, swimming, outdoor pursuits, gladiators, cooking, music, tug of war, bush craft and Paralympics are just some of the things your child could get up to.</p>
<p>The activities offered give children the chance to learn and experience new things that might not be available to them throughout the school year. It can be a life-changing experience that helps children to grow physically, mentally and socially &ndash; all whilst having fun!</p>
<p>Our camps take place at the following venues:</p>
<p><strong>Oxford High School</strong></p>
<p><strong>West Oxford Camp</strong></p>
<p>Oxford Active are offering Oxford University staff and student parents a 10% discount on all published prices.&nbsp; Childcare vouchers are also accepted.&nbsp; Please visit <a href="http://www.active-camps.com/">http://www.active-camps.com/</a> for more information.</p>
<hr />
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><a href="http://www.admin.ox.ac.uk/eop/childcare/voucherscheme/" target="_blank" title="Childcare Vouchers">Childcare Voucher Scheme&nbsp; </a></strong></span></p>
<p>The Childcare Voucher Scheme can be used at the Oxford Active, Create, and Ultimate Activity Camps&nbsp;holiday playschemes.&nbsp;</p>
